Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Remove the @SlooOW Stone Oven White Baguette{1} from the packaging and pop onto a #baking tray{}. Bake on the top shelf of your oven until toasted and golden, ~{10-12%mins}. Once baked, allow to cool, ~{5%mins}.

Meanwhile, chop the @potatoes{450%g} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide chips (no need to peel).

Pop the chips onto a large baking tray. Drizzle with oil, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

Bake on the middle shelf until golden, ~{30-35%mins}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). In a large #bowl{}, combine the garlic, @breadcrumbs{10%g}, @salt{1/4%tsp} and @water{2%tbsp} for the breadcrumbs, then add the @British pork mince{240%g}. Season with pepper and mix together with your hands.

Roll into evenly-sized balls, 5 per person.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Once your baguette is out of the oven, pop the meatballs onto another large baking tray and bake on the top shelf until browned on the outside and cooked through, ~{12-15%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: The meatballs are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

While the meatballs and chips are in the oven, grate the @mature cheddar cheese{60%g}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @tomato puree{30%g} and @vegan 'Nduja{3/4%sachet}. Fry, stirring vigorously, for ~{1%min}.

> Add less 'Nduja if you'd prefer things milder.

Stir in the @sugar{1%tsp} and @water{100%ml} for the sauce. Bring to the boil, then simmer until thickened slightly, ~{2-3%mins}.

Once cooked, stir the meatballs through the tomato sauce. Add the @butter{20%g} and stir until melted, ~{1%min}. Remove from the heat.

Halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125%g}(halved). Slice the baguette in half widthways and then slice each half lengthways to make 1 half baguette per person.

Lay your baguette halves on one of the baking trays. Sprinkle over the cheese on the cut sides of the lids.

Bake on the middle shelf until the cheese has melted and the bases are lightly toasted, ~{2-3%mins}, then remove from the oven.

Spoon the meatballs and tomato sauce over the baguette bases. Drizzle over the @pesto{32%g}, then sandwich shut with the cheesy lids.

When everything's ready, plate up your meatball subs. Share the @baby leaf mix{50%g} and baby plum tomatoes between your plates and drizzle over the @balsamic glaze{12%ml}.

Serve with the chips and @mayonnaise{2%tbsp} on the side for dipping. Enjoy!